				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\varphi$$\end{document}φ between randomly chosen pairs of vertices. As illustrated in Figure S3 (Supplemental Information), the resulting network features \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$2 \varphi {L}^{2}$$\end{document}2φL2 long-distance links, with mean coordination number \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
